description.narrative: The overall program objective is to improve the security, reliability and quality of energy supply, and, therefore, facilitate unimpeded operation of the energy market, both domestically and internationally. The main objective of the Hydropower Rehabilitation Project is to improve operational stability and reliability of power supply by increasing regulating capacity, efficiency and safety of hydroelectric plants, and, therefore, facilitate unimpeded operation and opening up of the electricity market. Additional objective is to support the Ministry of Fuel and Energy and NERC in preparing and implementing the Energy Sector Reform and Development Program, including the Wholesale Electricity Market (WEM) concept.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :LA 4.03 (a) | Description :Borrower to ensure for FY06 and thereafter that tariffs for UHE are adequate to coverproject cofinancing needs | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :LA 4.03 (b) | Description :Borrower to ensure distribution of funds due from Energomarket to UHE in a timely andadequate manner and in accordance with algorithm in place | Frequency :Quarterly
Finance Agreement :LA 4.03 (c) | Description :Borrower to introduce a two-tier tariff for UHE satisfactory to the Bank | Due Date:30-Dec-2005

Finance Agreement :LA 4.03 (d) | Description :Borrower to introduce, in parallel with suitable development of the balancingmechanism for WEM, a system service charge to be paidto UHE | Due Date :31-Dec-2015
Finance Agreement :LA Schedule 5, Section A, 1 | Description :Borrower to maintain throughout project implementation the Commissionfor Energy Sector Reform and Development | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :LA Schedule 5, Section A, 2 | Description :Borrower, through MFE and UHE, to maintain the EPCU and the PIU untilproject completion | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :PA 4.03 (a) | Description :UHE to maintain a debt service coverage ratio of at least 1.5 during the projectperiod | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :PA 4.04 (a) | Description :UHE to maintain a self-financing ratio of at least 15% during the project period |Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :PA 4.05 | Description :UHE to carry out a revaluation of its assets in accordance with terms of reference andconsultants satisfactory to the Bank | Due Date :10-May-2009
Finance Agreement :PA, Schedule 2, Section B, 1 | Description :UHE to implement the requirements of the Environmental ManagementPlan | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :PA, Schedule 2, Section B, 2 (v) | Description :UHE to have periodic dam safety inspections performed bypersonnel of the Dam Safety Center | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section B, 2 | Description :UHE to establish an adequately staffed Dam Safety Center under TORacceptable to the Bank. | Due Date :30-Dec-2005
